org.apache.abdera2.protocol.client
Class Session

java.lang.Object
  org.apache.abdera2.protocol.client.Session

public class Session
extends Object

A client session. Session's MUST NOT be used by more than one Thread of execution as a time as multiple threads would stomp all over the shared session context. It is critical to completely consume each ClientResponse before executing an additional request on the same session.

public ClientResponse post(String uri,
                           org.apache.abdera2.model.Entry entry,
                           org.apache.http.entity.mime.content.ContentBody media)
Sends an HTTP POST request to the specified URI. It uses the media and entry parameters to create a multipart/related object. If the contentType is not provided this method tries to get it from the type attribute of the entry content.

Parameters:
uri - The request URI
entry - The entry that will be sent as the first element of the multipart/related object
media - The media object that will be sent as the second element of the multipart/related object
